刑期如同...
An ice age here...

01:55:38.014 --> 01:55:41.065 align:middle line:90%
冰河时代
million years of mountain building there.

01:55:41.065 --> 01:55:45.032 align:middle line:90%
地质学探讨压力及时间
Geology is the study of pressure and time.

01:55:45.032 --> 01:55:48.005 align:middle line:90%
这就是凿通的关键
That's all it takes, really.

01:55:48.005 --> 01:55:49.079 align:middle line:90%
压力...
Pressure...

01:55:49.079 --> 01:55:52.039 align:middle line:90%
和时间
and time.

01:55:52.039 --> 01:55:58.026 align:middle line:90%
和一张够大的海报
That and a big goddamn poster.

01:55:58.026 --> 01:55:59.093 align:middle line:90%
就我说的
Like I said...

01:55:59.093 --> 01:56:06.074 align:middle line:90%
在牢里  没事也得找事做
in prison, a man will do anything to keep his mind occupied.

01:56:06.074 --> 01:56:12.008 align:middle line:90%
原来的安迪的嗜好...
Seems Andy's favorite hobby was toting his wall out into the exercise yard...

01:56:12.008 --> 01:56:15.031 align:middle line:90%
就是一点一滴倾倒废土
a handful at a time.

01:56:15.031 --> 01:56:17.058 align:middle line:90%
大概就在汤米死后...
I guess after Tommy was killed...

01:56:17.058 --> 01:56:20.075 align:middle line:90%
安迪决定不再久留
Andy decided he'd been here long enough.

01:56:20.075 --> 01:56:24.006 align:middle line:90%
动作快  我要回家
Lickety-split.I want to get home.

01:56:24.006 --> 01:56:47.055 align:middle line:90%
马上就好了
I'm just about finished, sir.

01:56:47.055 --> 01:56:56.079 align:middle line:90%
今晚要存三笔
Three deposits tonight.

01:56:56.079 --> 01:56:59.029 align:middle line:90%
安迪遵命行事
Andy did like he was told.

01:56:59.029 --> 01:57:06.047 align:middle line:90%
把鞋子擦的雪亮
Buffed those shoes to a high mirror-shine.

01:57:06.047 --> 01:57:09.007 align:middle line:90%
警卫都没注意
The guards simply didn't notice.

01:57:09.007 --> 01:57:10.074 align:middle line:90%
我也没有
Neither did I.

01:57:10.074 --> 01:57:12.047 align:middle line:90%
说真的
I mean, seriously...

01:57:12.047 --> 01:59:19.003 align:middle line:90%
谁会注意别人的鞋子
how often do you really look at a man's shoes?

01:59:19.003 --> 01:59:22.043 align:middle line:90%
安迪就这样爬向自由
Andy crawled to freedom through 500 yards...

01:59:22.043 --> 01:59:26.077 align:middle line:90%
在恶臭中匍匐五百码
of shit-smelling foulness I can't even imagine.

01:59:26.077 --> 01:59:33.051 align:middle line:90%
要我爬才不干
Or maybe I just don't want to.

01:59:33.051 --> 01:59:36.038 align:middle line:90%
五百码
Five hundred yards.

01:59:36.038 --> 01:59:40.009 align:middle line:90%
五座橄榄球场宽
That's the length of five football fields.

01:59:40.009 --> 02:00:37.088 align:middle line:90%
几乎长达半里
Just shy of half a mile.

02:00:37.088 --> 02:00:42.078 align:middle line:90%
次日清晨  在拉寇儿坦露她的秘密之时...
The next morning, right about the time Raquel was spilling her secret...

02:00:42.078 --> 02:00:45.085 align:middle line:90%
一个从未现世的人
a man nobody ever laid eyes on before...

02:00:45.085 --> 02:00:49.002 align:middle line:90%
走进缅因国家银行
strolled into the Maine National Bank.

02:00:49.002 --> 02:00:52.076 align:middle line:90%
在那之前  他不是实体
Until that moment, he didn't exist.

02:00:52.076 --> 02:00:55.053 align:middle line:90%
-只存在于文件上  -有何干贵?
-Except on paper. -May I help you?

02:00:55.053 --> 02:00:57.066 align:middle line:90%
他各种证件都有
He had all the proper ID...

02:00:57.066 --> 02:01:01.080 align:middle line:90%
驾照  出生证  社会保险卡
driver's license, birth certificate,Social Security card...

02:01:01.080 --> 02:01:04.054 align:middle line:90%
签名分毫不差
And the signature was a spot-on match.

02:01:04.054 --> 02:01:07.084 align:middle line:90%
失去您的生意令我真心遗憾
I must say I'm sorry to be losing your business.

02:01:07.084 --> 02:01:10.038 align:middle line:90%
祝您侨居愉快
I hope you'll enjoy living abroad.

02:01:10.038 --> 02:01:12.014 align:middle line:90%
谢谢
Thank you.

02:01:12.014 --> 02:01:14.021 align:middle line:90%
一定的
I'm sure I will.

02:01:14.021 --> 02:01:17.075 align:middle line:90%
这是银行本票  就这样吗?
Here's your cashier's check, sir.Will there be anything else?

02:01:17.075 --> 02:01:19.032 align:middle line:90%
麻烦你
Please.

02:01:19.032 --> 02:01:22.032 align:middle line:90%
帮我寄出去好吗?
Would you add this to your outgoing mail?

02:01:22.032 --> 02:01:25.032 align:middle line:90%
乐意之至
I'd be happy to.

02:01:25.032 --> 02:01:27.059 align:middle line:90%
-再会  -保重
Good day, sir.

02:01:27.059 --> 02:01:32.050 align:middle line:90%
那天上午史帝文斯先后去了十多家银行
Mr. Stevens visited nearly a dozen banks in the Portland area that morning.

02:01:32.050 --> 02:01:34.030 align:middle line:90%
总共加起来
All told, he blew town...

02:01:34.030 --> 02:01:39.084 align:middle line:90%
提走了诺顿的37万美金黑钱
with better than $370,000 of Warden Norton's money.

02:01:39.084 --> 02:01:49.085 align:middle line:90%
作为十九年冤狱的补偿
Severance pay for 19 years.

02:01:49.085 --> 02:01:52.045 align:middle line:90%
早上好 这里是波特兰日报
Good morning, Portland Daily Bugle.

02:01:52.045 --> 02:02:03.016 align:middle line:84%
肖申克监狱  贪污谋杀

02:02:03.016 --> 02:02:21.078 align:middle line:84%
主的审判迅速降临

02:02:21.078 --> 02:02:44.090 align:middle line:84%
亲爱的典狱长  你说的对  得救之道  就在其中

02:02:44.090 --> 02:02:48.011 align:middle line:90%
你是海利吗?  你有权保持沉默
Byron Hadley? You have the right to remain silent.

02:02:48.011 --> 02:02:52.098 align:middle line:90%
从现在起 你所说的一切 都将可能成为法庭上对你不利的证词
If you give up this right, anything you say can be held against you in court.

02:02:52.098 --> 02:02:57.065 align:middle line:90%
当时我没有在场  后来听说...
I wasn't there to see, but I hear Byron Hadley sobbed like a girl...

02:02:57.065 --> 02:03:05.002 align:middle line:90%
海利利被人带走的时候竟然哭得像个老娘们
when they took him away.

02:03:05.002 --> 02:03:24.038 align:middle line:90%
诺顿却无意乖乖就范
Norton had no intention of going that quietly.

02:03:24.038 --> 02:03:25.091 align:middle line:90%
诺顿
Samuel Norton.

02:03:25.091 --> 02:03:31.078 align:middle line:90%
诺顿  我们有逮捕令  开门
We have a warrant for your arrest. Open up.

02:03:31.078 --> 02:03:34.072 align:middle line:90%
把门打开
Open the door.

02:03:34.072 --> 02:03:45.066 align:middle line:90%
我不清楚哪一把
I'm not sure which key.

02:03:45.066 --> 02:03:59.058 align:middle line:90%
诺顿 拒捕是罪上加罪
Make it easy on yourself, Norton!

02:03:59.058 --> 02:04:03.025 align:middle line:90%
我猜他脑中最后一件事...
I like to think the last thing that went through his head...

02:04:03.025 --> 02:04:05.005 align:middle line:90%
除了枪子儿...
other than that bullet...

02:04:05.005 --> 02:04:11.099 align:middle line:90%
就是在想安迪为何能整倒他
was to wonder how the hell Andy Dufresne ever got the best of him.

02:04:11.099 --> 02:04:15.073 align:middle line:90%
典狱长见阎王之后不久
Not long after the warden deprived us of his company...

02:04:15.073 --> 02:04:19.026 align:middle line:90%
我收到一张明信片
I got a postcard in the mail.

02:04:19.026 --> 02:04:22.030 align:middle line:90%
没写字  但有邮戳
It was blank,but the postmark said...

02:04:22.030 --> 02:04:24.097 align:middle line:90%
来自德州汉考克堡
Fort Hancock, Texas.

02:04:24.097 --> 02:04:26.060 align:middle line:90%
汉考克堡
Fort Hancock...

02:04:26.060 --> 02:04:28.074 align:middle line:90%
就在边境线上
right on the border.

02:04:28.074 --> 02:04:31.031 align:middle line:90%
是安迪出境的地方
That's where Andy crossed.

02:04:31.031 --> 02:04:35.078 align:middle line:90%
一想到 他开着敞篷车 疾驶而去的神情
When I picture him heading south in his own car with the top down...

02:04:35.078 --> 02:04:39.085 align:middle line:90%
我就忍不住发笑
it always makes me laugh.

02:04:39.085 --> 02:04:41.079 align:middle line:90%
安迪·杜弗伦
Andy Dufresne...

02:04:41.079 --> 02:04:44.002 align:middle line:90%
终于从臭气熏天的下水道里
who crawled through a river of shit...

02:04:44.002 --> 02:04:47.026 align:middle line:90%
清清白白的走了出来
and came out clean on the other side.

02:04:47.026 --> 02:04:49.043 align:middle line:90%
安迪·杜弗伦
Andy Dufresne...

02:04:49.043 --> 02:04:54.000 align:middle line:90%
向太平洋驶去
headed for the Pacific.

02:04:54.000 --> 02:04:56.037 align:middle line:90%
海利掐住他说...
Hadley's got him by the throat, right?

02:04:56.037 --> 02:05:00.037 align:middle line:90%
"他活的不耐烦了"
He says, "I believe this boy's about to have himself an accident."

02:05:00.037 --> 02:05:03.091 align:middle line:90%
老友们常聊起他
Those of us who knew him best talk about him often.

02:05:03.091 --> 02:05:05.081 align:middle line:90%
他那些惊人之举
I swear, the stuff he pulled...

02:05:05.081 --> 02:05:09.011 align:middle line:90%
"请我朋友喝啤酒吧"
"My friends could use a couple of beers."

02:05:09.011 --> 02:05:12.002 align:middle line:90%
真的做到了
And he got it!

02:05:12.002 --> 02:05:14.069 align:middle line:90%
他走了  有时...
Sometimes it makes me sad, though...

02:05:14.069 --> 02:05:16.082 align:middle line:90%
令我感伤
Andy being gone.

02:05:16.082 --> 02:05:21.043 align:middle line:90%
有些鸟儿是不应该被关在笼子里的
I have to remind myself that some birds aren't meant to be caged.

02:05:21.043 --> 02:05:25.020 align:middle line:90%
因为它们的羽毛太丰润了
Their feathers are just too bright.

02:05:25.020 --> 02:05:27.037 align:middle line:90%
当他们飞走...
And when they fly away...

02:05:27.037 --> 02:05:32.084 align:middle line:90%
你会由衷地庆贺他获得自由
the part of you that knows it was a sin to lock them up does rejoice.

02:05:32.084 --> 02:05:34.057 align:middle line:90%
无奈的是...
But still...

02:05:34.057 --> 02:05:43.011 align:middle line:90%
你得继续在这乏味之地苟活
the place you live in is that much more drab and empty that they're gone.

02:05:43.011 --> 02:06:09.094 align:middle line:90%
我真怀念这位友伴
I guess I just miss my friend.

02:06:09.094 --> 02:06:16.095 align:middle line:90%
请坐
Please sit down.

02:06:16.095 --> 02:06:19.005 align:middle line:90%
阿里斯瑞丁
Ellis Boyd Redding...

02:06:19.005 --> 02:06:23.012 align:middle line:90%
根据你的材料 你的终身监禁已经服满40年
your files say you've served 40 years of a life sentence.

02:06:23.012 --> 02:06:27.013 align:middle line:90%
你改过自新了吗?
You feel you've been rehabilitated?

02:06:27.013 --> 02:06:30.073 align:middle line:90%
改过自新?
Rehabilitated?

02:06:30.073 --> 02:06:33.063 align:middle line:90%
噢 让我想想
Well, now, let me see.

02:06:33.063 --> 02:06:38.007 align:middle line:90%
我不大明白这个词的含义
I don't have any idea what that means.

02:06:38.007 --> 02:06:40.091 align:middle line:90%
就是说准备好重返社会
It means you're ready to rejoin society...

02:06:40.091 --> 02:06:45.041 align:middle line:90%
我当然明白你的意思 年轻人
I know what you think it means, sonny.

02:06:45.041 --> 02:06:48.075 align:middle line:90%
对我而言 这只是个术语
To me it's just a made-up word.

02:06:48.075 --> 02:06:51.052 align:middle line:90%
就像政治家那些术语
A politician's word so that...

02:06:51.052 --> 02:06:55.052 align:middle line:90%
使你们穿西装打领带的...
young fellas like yourself can wear a suit and a tie...

02:06:55.052 --> 02:06:59.009 align:middle line:90%
有活干
and have a job.

02:06:59.009 --> 02:07:01.096 align:middle line:90%
你到底想了解什么?
What do you really want to know?

02:07:01.096 --> 02:07:04.036 align:middle line:90%
我后悔犯罪吗?
Am I sorry for what I did?

02:07:04.036 --> 02:07:07.043 align:middle line:90%
你后悔吗?
Well, are you?

02:07:07.043 --> 02:07:11.064 align:middle line:90%
我没有一天不后悔
There's not a day goes by I don't feel regret.

02:07:11.064 --> 02:07:18.058 align:middle line:90%
但并非受惩罚才后悔
Not because I'm in here or because you think I should.

02:07:18.058 --> 02:07:23.028 align:middle line:90%
我回首前尘往事
I look back on the way I was then...

02:07:23.028 --> 02:07:25.055 align:middle line:90%
那个
a young...

02:07:25.055 --> 02:07:32.006 align:middle line:90%
犯下重罪的小笨蛋
stupid kid who committed that terrible crime.

02:07:32.006 --> 02:07:35.069 align:middle line:90%
我想跟他沟通
I want to talk to him.

02:07:35.069 --> 02:07:38.090 align:middle line:90%
我试图讲道理
I want to try and talk some sense to him.

02:07:38.090 --> 02:07:42.093 align:middle line:90%
让他明了
Tell him the way things are.

02:07:42.093 --> 02:07:46.057 align:middle line:90%
但我办不到
But I can't.

02:07:46.057 --> 02:07:49.077 align:middle line:90%
那个少年早就不见了
That kid's long gone...

02:07:49.077 --> 02:07:53.095 align:middle line:90%
只剩下我垂老之躯
and this old man is all that's left.

02:07:53.095 --> 02:07:56.078 align:middle line:90%
我得接受事实
I got to live with that.

02:07:56.078 --> 02:07:58.085 align:middle line:90%
改过自新?
Rehabilitated?

02:07:58.085 --> 02:08:01.062 align:middle line:90%
狗屁不通的词
It's just a bullshit word.

02:08:01.062 --> 02:08:07.063 align:middle line:90%
你盖章吧  别浪费我的时间
So you go on and stamp your forms,sonny, and stop wasting my time.

02:08:07.063 --> 02:08:10.023 align:middle line:90%
告诉你一句实话
Because to tell you the truth...

02:08:10.023 --> 02:08:25.044 align:middle line:90%
我他妈的不在乎
I don't give a shit.

02:08:25.044 --> 02:09:21.070 align:middle line:90%
核准
Approved

02:09:21.070 --> 02:09:38.075 align:middle line:90%
老布到此一游
Brook was here

02:09:38.075 --> 02:09:43.009 align:middle line:90%
谢谢你
Here you go, miss.

02:09:43.009 --> 02:09:49.093 align:middle line:90%
可以上厕所吗?
Restroom break?

02:09:49.093 --> 02:09:55.050 align:middle line:90%
别要尿尿就来报告  要去就去  懂吗?
You don't need to ask me every time you need to go take a piss. Just go.

02:09:55.050 --> 02:10:07.051 align:middle line:90%
是的
yes

02:10:07.051 --> 02:10:11.042 align:middle line:90%
我报告了40年
Forty years I've been asking permission to piss.

02:10:11.042 --> 02:10:17.092 align:middle line:90%
没报告  一滴也挤不出
I can't squeeze a drop without say-so.

02:10:17.092 --> 02:10:21.076 align:middle line:90%
我得面对残酷的事实
There's a harsh truth to face.

02:10:21.076 --> 02:10:32.054 align:middle line:90%
我根本混不下去
No way I'm going to make it on the outside.

02:10:32.054 --> 02:10:37.004 align:middle line:90%
我一心想违犯假释
All I do anymore is think of ways to break my parole...

02:10:37.004 --> 02:10:44.072 align:middle line:90%
也许能重返肖申克
so maybe they'd send me back.

02:10:44.072 --> 02:10:48.005 align:middle line:90%
活在恐惧中真是糟糕
Terrible thing, to live in fear.

02:10:48.005 --> 02:10:49.092 align:middle line:90%
布鲁克体会过
Brooks Hatlen knew it.

02:10:49.092 --> 02:10:53.046 align:middle line:90%
他看透了
Knew it all too well.

02:10:53.046 --> 02:10:57.030 align:middle line:90%
我只想回到有意义的地方
All I want is to be back where things make sense.

02:10:57.030 --> 02:11:02.003 align:middle line:90%
不必整天担惊受怕
Where I won't have to be afraid all the time.

02:11:02.003 --> 02:11:05.084 align:middle line:90%
只有一件事阻止了我
Only one thing stops me.

02:11:05.084 --> 02:11:28.076 align:middle line:90%
我向安迪做的承诺
A promise I made to Andy.

02:11:28.076 --> 02:11:40.050 align:middle line:90%
到了
There it is.

02:11:40.050 --> 02:11:51.022 align:middle line:90%
非常感谢您
Much obliged, sir.

02:11:51.022 --> 02:15:21.049 align:middle line:90%
巴克斯顿
Buxton

02:15:21.049 --> 02:15:22.099 align:middle line:90%
亲爱的瑞德
Dear Red:

02:15:22.099 --> 02:15:25.066 align:middle line:90%
见到这封信的时候 你已经出狱了
If you're reading this,you've gotten out...

02:15:25.066 --> 02:15:30.000 align:middle line:90%
既然走了这么远的路 干脆再走远一点吧
and if you've come this far,maybe you'd come a bit further.

02:15:30.000 --> 02:15:34.077 align:middle line:90%
你还记得那个地方的名字,是吗?
You remember the name of the town, don't you?

02:15:34.077 --> 02:15:37.091 align:middle line:90%
芝华塔尼欧
Zihuatanejo.

02:15:37.091 --> 02:15:42.001 align:middle line:90%
你能帮我实现计划
I could use a good man to help me get my project on wheels.

02:15:42.001 --> 02:15:46.035 align:middle line:90%
我备妥棋盘等着你
I'll keep an eye out for you,and the chessboard ready.

02:15:46.035 --> 02:15:48.009 align:middle line:90%
记住,瑞德.
Remember, Red...

02:15:48.009 --> 02:15:50.039 align:middle line:90%
心怀希望是一件好事
hope is a good thing...

02:15:50.039 --> 02:15:52.059 align:middle line:90%
也许是最好的事
maybe the best of things.

02:15:52.059 --> 02:15:55.029 align:middle line:90%
心怀希望 就永远有希望
And no good thing ever dies.

02:15:55.029 --> 02:15:58.036 align:middle line:90%
希望这封信 能让我再次见到你
I will be hoping that this letter finds you...

02:15:58.036 --> 02:16:00.060 align:middle line:90%
一个健壮的你
and finds you well.

02:16:00.060 --> 02:16:02.003 align:middle line:90%
你的朋友
Your friend...

02:16:02.003 --> 02:16:37.003 align:middle line:90%
安迪
Andy.

02:16:37.003 --> 02:16:38.097 align:middle line:90%
要么忙于生存
"Get busy living...

02:16:38.097 --> 02:16:43.057 align:middle line:90%
要么赶着去死
or get busy dying."

02:16:43.057 --> 02:16:48.031 align:middle line:90%
这话真他妈的精辟
That's goddamn right.

02:16:48.031 --> 02:16:50.098 align:middle line:84%
瑞德也来过

02:16:50.098 --> 02:16:53.035 align:middle line:90%
这是生平第二次
For the second time in my life...

02:16:53.035 --> 02:16:56.099 align:middle line:90%
我又犯了罪
I'm guilty of committing a crime.

02:16:56.099 --> 02:16:59.059 align:middle line:90%
违反假释出城
Parole violation.

02:16:59.059 --> 02:17:03.093 align:middle line:90%
我怀疑警方会设路障逮我
Of course I doubt they'll toss up any roadblocks for that.

02:17:03.093 --> 02:17:06.016 align:middle line:90%
我这种老贼可以免了
Not for an old crook like me.

02:17:06.016 --> 02:17:11.087 align:middle line:90%
德州汉考克堡
Fort Hancock, Texas, please.

02:17:11.087 --> 02:17:17.004 align:middle line:90%
我激动的坐不住不停地想
I find I'm so excited I can barely sit still or hold a thought in my head.

02:17:17.004 --> 02:17:20.058 align:middle line:90%
自由人才会这么兴奋吧
I think it's the excitement only a free man can feel.

02:17:20.058 --> 02:17:23.028 align:middle line:90%
踏上未知旅程的...
A free man at the start of a long journey...

02:17:23.028 --> 02:17:28.089 align:middle line:90%
自由人
whose conclusion is uncertain.

02:17:28.089 --> 02:17:33.006 align:middle line:90%
我希望成功越过边界
I hope I can make it across the border.

02:17:33.006 --> 02:17:37.096 align:middle line:90%
我希望能跟老友握握手
I hope to see my friend and shake his hand.

02:17:37.096 --> 02:17:43.087 align:middle line:90%
我希望太平洋如梦中一般蓝
I hope the Pacific is as blue as it has been in my dreams.

02:17:43.087 --> 02:18:19.020 align:middle line:90%
我希望...
I hope.

02:18:19.020 --> 02:18:24.020 align:middle line:84%
谨此纪念亚伦格林